12 C. The principal administrator of the state agency with which
13 the employee is employed shall so designate the status of the
14 employee in writing or provide a copy of the temporary authorization
15 to the Governor, the President Pro Tempore of the Oklahoma State
16 Senate and the Speaker of the Oklahoma House of Representatives.
17 Such employee status report shall also be provided to the State
